! Edit History

Browse and restore previous editing states via periodic snapshots.

!! Features

* ''Automatic snapshots'': Captures state periodically while editing
* ''Snapshot browser'': View list of snapshots with timestamps
* ''State restoration'': Restore any previous snapshot
* ''Selection preservation'': Restores cursor position with snapshot

!! Keyboard Shortcuts

|!Key |!Action |
|Ctrl+Alt+H |Open snapshot picker |

!! How It Works

# Snapshots are captured automatically every 800ms during editing
# Also captures on focus
# Up to 50 snapshots are kept (oldest discarded)
# Pick a snapshot to restore editor to that state

!! Snapshot Picker

Shows a numbered list with timestamps:

```
Pick snapshot index:
0: 10:23:45
1: 10:23:46
2: 10:23:48
...
```

Enter the index number to restore that state.

!! Configuration

|!Tiddler |!Values |!Default |
|`$:/config/Editor/EnableEditHistory` |`yes` / `no` |`no` |

!! Widget Attribute

```
<$edit-text enableEditHistory="yes"/>
```

!! Notes

* Snapshots are per editing session (lost on close)
* Separate from undo/redo stack
* Useful for recovering from accidental large deletions
* Disabled by default due to memory overhead